;ENGINEERED RESIDUE IN CHAIN A, GLN 130 TO ARG
ENGINEERED RESIDUE IN CHAIN B, GLN 130 TO ARG

REGULATORY SUBUNIT OF THE CYCLIN-DEPENDENT KINASE PAIR
(CDK9/CYCLIN T) COMPLEX, ALSO CALLED POSITIVE TRANSCRIPTION
ELONGATION FACTOR B (P-TEFB), WHICH IS PROPOSED TO FACILITATE THE
TRANSITION FROM ABORTIVE TO PRODUCTION ELONGATION BY
PHOSPHORYLATING THE CTD (CARBOXY-TERMINAL DOMAIN) OF THE LARGE
SUBUNIT OF RNA POLYMERASE II (RNAP II).
